</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="513741E1C1536451FAC94C9F6F84E869" pageId="509" pageNumber="510" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="FA42910B0254C92911BBC7BD34BBC0D9" pageId="509" pageNumber="510">
<taxonomicName id="61B2630783F72552120FF545D1822AAF" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Melanius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="509" pageNumber="510" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Melanius</taxonomicName>
Bonelli, 1810: Tabula Synoptica. Type species: 
<taxonomicName id="AFD11DAC2979D605131BD029CBF0B9DE" authorityName="Herbst" authorityYear="1784" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Carabus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="509" pageNumber="510" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aterrimus">
<emphasis id="13ECFDF5E98B86A3CAC10BE871F86C4B" italics="true" pageId="509" pageNumber="510">Carabus aterrimus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Herbst, 1784 by subsequent monotypy in Latreille (1816: 194). Etymology. Uncertain, possibly from the Greek 
<emphasis id="BE824DD76777D6A23A2DD1FE0DFED90D" italics="true" pageId="509" pageNumber="510">melanos</emphasis>
(black), alluding to the black coloration of adults of the species in the hands of Bonelli [masculine].
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D0B9AA7B210E5316C703DABFA207601D" pageId="509" pageNumber="510">
<taxonomicName id="DA253B72073C691257363E80C81CB0FB" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Omaseus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="509" pageNumber="510" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Omaseus</taxonomicName>
Dejean, 1821: 12. Type species: 
<taxonomicName id="305EE420DAA003E70B6F53F4807D17CF" authorityName="Herbst" authorityYear="1784" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Carabus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="509" pageNumber="510" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aterrimus">
<emphasis id="9F8366A9B63B9D79C9A63F5008D5DD84" italics="true" pageId="509" pageNumber="510">Carabus aterrimus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Herbst, 1784 designated by Curtis (1824: plate 15). Etymology. Unknown [masculine]. The name was proposed by Franz Anton Ziegler and made available by Dejean.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D1AB35FF39654E20CD66EF170EC02E78" pageId="509" pageNumber="510">
<taxonomicName id="72B3E64F7E9008E220C0571888B7DA1B" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Lyperus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="509" pageNumber="510" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Lyperus</taxonomicName>
Chaudoir, 1838: 12. Type species: 
<taxonomicName id="3C3A60BE84432D20DEA6EB107F48975A" authorityName="Herbst" authorityYear="1784" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Carabus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="509" pageNumber="510" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aterrimus">
<emphasis id="C201B30EAC85A50A799F39CF256C4E88" italics="true" pageId="509" pageNumber="510">Carabus aterrimus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Herbst, 1784 by original designation. Etymology (original). From Greek 
<emphasis id="1B2022A54501B09C1CE6A7B7AF00C4F3" italics="true" pageId="509" pageNumber="510">lyperos</emphasis>
(painful, by extension sad) [masculine].
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="DF2B675DB0067F88AFACCA8036EAD41B" pageId="509" pageNumber="510">
<taxonomicName id="4A655F6C53A44A57AC0D9B08AFD787B2" authorityName="Motschoulsky" authorityYear="1850" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Lyperosomus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="509" pageNumber="510" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Lyperosomus</taxonomicName>
Motschulsky, 1850a: 47. Unnecessary replacement name for 
<taxonomicName id="E46E32BF63C6E5DFC6E97DE38591021D" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Lyperus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="509" pageNumber="510" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="0784C2F1BEAB1B046838429F6AD92137" italics="true" pageId="509" pageNumber="510">Lyperus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Chaudoir, 1838. Etymology. From Greek 
<emphasis id="7BA0105CA2972194078DD53B40F0C520" italics="true" pageId="509" pageNumber="510">lyperos</emphasis>
(painful, by extension sad) and 
<emphasis id="641CCFB8A2856F54BBDE81ADC4844C22" italics="true" pageId="509" pageNumber="510">soma</emphasis>
(body) [masculine].
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="83E394A9697EDD310C1CA6B2DAB69440" pageId="509" pageNumber="510">
<taxonomicName id="ED18656BDF3AB604C32834E79C9BDF15" authorityName="Tschitscherin" authorityYear="1900" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Metamelanius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="509" pageNumber="510" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Metamelanius</taxonomicName>
<normalizedToken id="CBA2D00C7AD4CE36855B867C00525D1D" originalValue="TschitschÃ©rine">Tschitscherine</normalizedToken>
, 1900b: 395. Type species: 
<taxonomicName id="FADCFD5AB5F8206AEAF6746E668E5508" authorityName="Dejean" authorityYear="1828" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Feronia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="509" pageNumber="510" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ebenina">
<emphasis id="C2595ABE3BB72388B4139CE07642E574" italics="true" pageId="509" pageNumber="510">Feronia ebenina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Dejean, 1828 by monotypy. Synonymy established by Lindroth (1966: 498). Etymology. From the Greek 
<emphasis id="83696FCF263D5986C32F5404E011CF93" italics="true" pageId="509" pageNumber="510">meta</emphasis>
(near, among) and the generic name 
<taxonomicName id="D0815377A053B3B7A6D94E8D36B51D09" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Melanius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="509" pageNumber="510" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="25421B1BB546A6896D3A7D3D3A84FFC9" italics="true" pageId="509" pageNumber="510">Melanius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
[
<emphasis id="6394D2328FF04F906845239CB11D645F" italics="true" pageId="509" pageNumber="510">q.v</emphasis>
.] [masculine].
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="CDC9F093FDC7907E118104EC416EA28F" pageId="509" pageNumber="510" type="diversity">
<paragraph id="77224720ABFCAFE2332874BD2FD2E82E" pageId="509" pageNumber="510">Diversity.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2BDBB3C43EDB091C663DBA4ADAA2E5EC" pageId="509" pageNumber="510">Eight species in the boreal and temperate regions of the Nearctic (three eastern species) and Palaearctic (five species, of which three occur in the Far East) Regions.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="665CD0A59FCA2462C6D447DA61CC3CA3" pageId="509" pageNumber="510" type="identification">
<paragraph id="B68194B1EED8168C8DAD3B402F4141D0" pageId="509" pageNumber="510">Identification.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="31712E356E53C81CF50283BEBE0D567B" pageId="509" pageNumber="510">Lindroth (1966) reviewed the North American species. One new species was described subsequently by Goulet and Bousquet (1983).</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
